data.enText: calculated by adding several amounts together, finding a total, and dividing the total by the number of amounts
data.chText: 平均的

data.enText: an average rate/cost/price
data.chText: 平均费率 / 成本 / 价格

data.enText: Average earnings are around £20 000 per annum.
data.chText: 年平均收入约为2万英镑。

data.enText: at an average speed of 100 miles per hour
data.chText: 以平均每小时100英里的速度

data.enText: typical or normal
data.chText: 典型的；正常的

data.enText: 40 hours is a fairly average working week for most people.
data.chText: 对大多数人来说，一周工作40小时是相当正常的。

data.enText: children of above/below average intelligence
data.chText: 高于 / 低于一般智力的儿童

data.enText: £20 for dinner is about average.
data.chText: 花20英镑吃正餐算是价格一般。

data.enText: ordinary; not special
data.chText: 普通的；平常的；一般的

data.enText: I was just an average sort of student.
data.chText: 我只是一个普通的学生。

data.enText: He was attractive and averagely intelligent.
data.chText: 他讨人喜欢，智力一般。

data.enText: the result of adding several amounts together, finding a total, and dividing the total by the number of amounts
data.chText: 平均数

data.enText: The average of 4, 5 and 9 is 6.
data.chText: 4、5、9三个数的平均数是6。

data.enText: Parents spend an average of $220 a year on toys.
data.chText: 父母为孩子买玩具的花费每年平均为220元。

data.enText: If I get an A on this essay, that will bring my average (= average mark/grade) up to a B+.
data.chText: 如果我的这篇论文得A，我的平均成绩就会提高到B+。

data.enText: a level which is usual
data.chText: 平均水平；一般水准

data.enText: Temperatures are above/below average for the time of year.
data.chText: 温度高于 / 低于此时的年平均温度。

data.enText: 400 people a year die of this disease on average .
data.chText: 平均每年有400人死于这种疾病。

data.enText: Class sizes in the school are below the national average .
data.chText: 这所学校班上的人数少于全国平均数。

data.enText: the law of averages
the principle that one thing will happen as often as another if you try enough times
data.chText: 平均律

data.enText: Keep applying and by the law of averages you'll get a job sooner or later.
data.chText: 继续申请吧，根据平均律你迟早会找到工作的。

data.enText: to be equal to a particular amount as an average
data.chText: 平均为

data.enText: Economic growth is expected to average 2% next year.
data.chText: 明年经济增长预计平均可达2%。

data.enText: Drivers in London can expect to average about 12 miles per hour (= to have that as their average speed) .
data.chText: 估计伦敦的驾车者平均时速为12英里。

data.enText: to calculate the average of sth
data.chText: 计算出…的平均数

data.enText: Earnings are averaged over the whole period.
data.chText: 所计算的是整个时期的平均收入。

data.enText: average out (at sth)
to result in an average amount over a period of time or when several things are considered
data.chText: 平均数为

data.enText: The cost should average out at about £6 per person.
data.chText: 费用应该是平均每人约6英镑。

data.enText: Sometimes I pay, sometimes he pays─it seems to average out (= result in us paying the same amount) .
data.chText: 有时我付钱，有时他付钱——看来两相持平。

data.enText: average sth↔out (at sth)
to calculate the average of sth
data.chText: 计算出…的平均数

ex.enText: She is in her early thirties and of average height.
The median age  of that group is 36.

synonyms.bx: 指处于中间位置的或在一组数值中居中的。

ex.enText: This cloth is of medium quality.
The red cap is of a medium size.
ex.chText: 那顶红色的帽子是中号的。

ex.enText: Fry the fish over a medium heat.

synonyms.bx: 通常用于大小、水平、数量等。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：中间的，中等的

data.enText: Sometimes I pay, sometimes he pays─it seems to average out (= result in us paying the same amount) .

the principle that one thing will happen as often as another if you try enough times

data.chText: 继续申请吧，根据平均律你迟早会找到工作的。

tr: an intermediate scale value regarded as normal or usual
example: he is about average in height
the snowfall this month is below average

tr: a statistic describing the location of a distribution
example: it set the norm for American homes

tr: (sports) the ratio of successful performances to opportunities

example: He averaged a C

tr: amount to or come to an average, without loss or gain
example: The number of hours I work per work averages out to 40

tr: lacking special distinction, rank, or status
example: average people
the ordinary (or common) man in the street

tr: around the middle of a scale of evaluation
example: an orange of average size
intermediate capacity
medium bombers

tr: approximating the statistical norm or average or expected value
example: the average income in New England is below that of the nation
of average height for his age
the mean annual rainfall

tr: relating to or constituting the middle value of an ordered set of values (or the average of the middle two in a set with an even number of values)
example: the median value of 17, 20, and 36 is 20
the median income for the year was $15,000

tr: relating to or constituting the most frequent value in a distribution
example: the modal age at which American novelists reach their peak is 30
a novel of average merit
only a fair performance of the sonata
in fair health
the caliber of the students has gone from mediocre to above average
the performance was middling at best

example.ex: Take the average of those ratios and multiply by a hundred.
example.tran: 算出那些比率的平均值再乘以100。

example.ex: The average price of goods rose by just 2.2%...
example.tran: 商品平均价格只上涨了2.2％。

example.ex: Of America's million millionaires in 1985, the average age was 63.
example.tran: 1985年美国上百万的百万富翁的平均年龄是63岁。

value.def: An average is the result that you get when you add two or more numbers together and divide the total by the number of numbers you added together.

example.ex: It takes an average of ten weeks for a house sale to be completed.
example.tran: 售出一幢房子平均需要10周的时间。

value.def: You use average to refer to a number or size that varies but is always approximately the same.

example.ex: The average adult man burns 1,500 to 2,000 calories per day...
example.tran: 普通成年男子每天消耗的热量为1,500到2,000卡路里。

example.ex: Packaging is about a third of what is found in an average British dustbin.
example.tran: 英国垃圾桶里平均约有1/3是产品包装。

value.def: An average person or thing is typical or normal.

example.ex: Most areas suffered more rain than usual, with Northern Ireland getting double the average for the month.
example.tran: 大部分地区降雨超过通常水平，北爱尔兰地区本月的降水量则为平均值的两倍。
一杯啤酒价格通常为2.2英镑。

value.def: An amount or quality that is the average is the normal amount or quality for a particular group of things or people.
Something that is average is neither very good nor very bad, usually when you had hoped it would be better.

example.ex: Most children are not geniuses or stars. They just do averagely well...
example.tran: 大多数孩子既不是天才也不是明星，他们只是表现平平。

example.ex: The songs are performed averagely, although the band seem to be enjoying themselves.
example.tran: 歌曲演唱得很一般，不过乐队好像很自我陶醉。
我们的平均时速是每小时42英里。

value.def: To average a particular amount means to do, get, or produce that amount as an average over a period of time.

example.ex: American shares rose, on average, by 38%...
example.tran: 美国股票价格平均上涨了38％。

example.ex: On an average we would be spending £300 per day.
example.tran: 平均下来，我们每天要花费300英镑。

value.def: You say on average or on an average to indicate that a number is the average of several numbers.

example.ex: On average, American firms remain the most productive in the world.
example.tran: 总体来讲，美国公司在全球范围内还是产值最高。

value.def: If you say that something is true on average, you mean that it is generally true.
